title: Apple’s App Store problem in the Netherlands keeps getting worse
content:
Earlier today we reported that Apple was fined $5.6 million for not complying with a new regulation in the Netherlands that forces tech companies to let dating apps offer alternative payment methods. Now another Dutch group has joined the fight against the App Store, claiming that Apple charges high commissions from developers.

more…

description: Another Dutch group has joined the fight against the App Store as it claims that Apple has high commissions.
